## 4. Sets

Julia has a built-in **Set** collection type as part of Base collections. The collections documentation covers set-like collection behavior alongside dictionaries and other collection utilities. ([docs.julialang.org][1])

```julia
skills = Set(["boxing", "Muay Thai", "karate", "Muay Thai"])
println(skills)
```

Even though `"Muay Thai"` appears twice, the set keeps only one copy.

Membership check:

```julia
println("boxing" in skills)
println("MMA" in skills)
```

Sets are useful when you care about:

* uniqueness
* membership checks
* removing duplicates

