## Indexing reminder

Julia uses **1-based indexing**.

```julia
colors = ["red", "blue", "green"]
println(colors[1])  # red
println(colors[2])  # blue
println(colors[3])  # green
```

That is one of the biggest differences from Python, TypeScript, Rust, and Go, and it lines up more with R. ([docs.julialang.org][2])

